{"id":351802,"avatar":"//lain.bgm.tv/pic/user/m/000/21/04/210454.jpg","floor":"#1","group":"靠谱人生茶话会","groupHref":"/group/boring","groupThumb":"//lain.bgm.tv/pic/icon/m/000/00/03/364.jpg","message":"你用日语我好歹还能认识几个汉字，换成罗马音就日语苦手一脸懵逼了（假名也能读几个，换成罗马音还要反应下）。<br><br>用罗马音作标题的意义何在？既不会帮助本国人理解标题，也不会帮助外国人理解标题，充其量让外国人会读日语标题，可这又有什么意义呢？<br><br>咱中文的歌出口到国外也不会把汉语拼音当成标题吧。<img src=\"/img/smiles/tv/15.gif\" smileid=\"54\" alt=\"(bgm38)\"><br><br>例子：<br>《隐之王》ED1：《<a href=\"https://music.163.com/#/song?id=566405\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow external noopener noreferrer\" class=\"l\">HIKARI</a>》<br>《微笑的闪士》OP：《<a href=\"https://music.163.com/#/song?id=26307817\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow external noopener noreferrer\" class=\"l\">KOHAKU</a>》<br>黑川沙良《<a href=\"https://music.163.com/#/song?id=33789470\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow external noopener noreferrer\" class=\"l\">HANABI</a>》（一搜还有点多，《死神》也有这么一首b38）<br>《怪化猫》ED1：<a href=\"https://music.163.com/#/song?id=22788400\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow external noopener noreferrer\" class=\"l\">NATSUNOHAHA</a><br>生物股长《<a href=\"https://music.163.com/#/song?id=719102\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow external noopener noreferrer\" class=\"l\">SAKURA</a>》（这个太普遍了，暂且认为没有对理解没什么副作用吧。）<br>梶浦由记经常用。比如《翼》的插曲《<a href=\"https://music.163.com/#/song?id=593040\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow external noopener noreferrer\" class=\"l\">TSUBASA</a>》<br>别野加奈《<a href=\"https://music.163.com/#/song?id=421807898\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow external noopener noreferrer\" class=\"l\">unomi</a>》<br>mamerico《<a href=\"https://music.163.com/#/song?id=26131195\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow external noopener noreferrer\" class=\"l\">KIRARI FUTARI</a>》（这张专辑的好多歌都是）<br>不知道为啥网易上冈崎律子《Rain or Shine》还有DoCo（《乱马½》的声优组合）的好几张专辑的日语标题的歌名都是罗马音，但是bgm上还是日语。 ","time":"2019-7-29 12:59","title":"为什么很多日语歌的标题是罗马音呢？","userId":"mp4spig","userName":"狂犬榨汁姬艾莉丝","userSign":"(いつでも微笑みを)"}